<topic id='business_definition_pharmacy_premises.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Pharmacy Premises - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
 can be an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 or an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation_site">ORGANISATION SITE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
 is a location where medicinal drugs are dispensed and sold.  </p>
  <p>
      <b>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
 Registration of 
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
:    </b>
  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
 (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">GPhC</xref>
) maintains a register of 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
 if the principal activity at the premises is the retail sale or supply of Pharmacy (P) medicines and / or Prescription Only Medicines (POMs). They are not primarily concerned with NHS Prescriptions.  </p>
  <p>
Once a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
 is registered with the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
 it is allocated a registration number which uniquely identifies each registered 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
. This registration number is a 7 digit number starting with the number 1.  </p>
  <p>
All 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
 that are currently registered with the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
 are listed on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council_register">General Pharmaceutical Council Register</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For further information on 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
 registration, see the 
    <xref href="https://www.pharmacyregulation.org/"
            scope="external"
            format="html">General Pharmaceutical Council website</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <b>
         <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
 (
      <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
               scope="external"
               format="html">ODS</xref>
) Codes:    </b>
  </p>
  <p>
To be able to dispense NHS Prescriptions, the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_pharmacy_premises">Pharmacy Premises</xref>
 requires an 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
 code in addition to the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_general_pharmaceutical_council">General Pharmaceutical Council</xref>
 registration number.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
 allocates the following codes:  </p>
